# 🏥 Health Portal - Syndromic Surveillance System

[![Node.js](https://img.shields.io/badge/Node.js-18+-green.svg)](https://nodejs.org/)
[![Express.js](https://img.shields.io/badge/Express.js-4.18+-blue.svg)](https://expressjs.com/)
[![MongoDB](https://img.shields.io/badge/MongoDB-6.0+-green.svg)](https://www.mongodb.com/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](LICENSE)

A comprehensive healthcare data management system with ML-powered syndromic surveillance capabilities. This system provides real-time analysis of patient symptoms to help healthcare professionals identify potential health threats and provide appropriate care.

## ✨ Features

### 🧠 ML-Powered Analysis
- **Real-time Risk Scoring**: 0-100% risk assessment
- **Syndrome Prediction**: Respiratory, Gastrointestinal, Cardiac, Neurological
- **Confidence Levels**: AI confidence in predictions
- **Smart Recommendations**: Personalized care suggestions
- **Flagging System**: Automatic high-risk case identification

### 🔐 Security & Authentication
- JWT-based authentication
- Password hashing with bcrypt
- Input validation and sanitization
- Rate limiting and CORS protection
- Role-based access control

### 📊 Comprehensive Dashboard
- Interactive symptom reporting
- Real-time ML analysis display
- Patient history tracking
- Surveillance data visualization
- Trend analysis and alerts

### 🚀 Modern Tech Stack
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB
- **Frontend**: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+)
- **ML Engine**: Rule-based analysis with extensible architecture
- **Security**: Helmet, bcrypt, express-validator
- **Documentation**: Comprehensive guides and API docs

## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v14 or higher)
- MongoDB
- npm or yarn

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/monish885-sys/healthportal.git
   cd healthportal
   ```

2. **Start the application:**
   ```bash
   ./scripts/start.sh
   ```

3. **Access the application:**
   - **Main App**: http://localhost:3000
   - **Test Login**: http://localhost:3000/test-login.html

### Default Login Credentials
- **Email**: `john.doe@example.com`
